!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

underneath /ˌʌndəˈniːθ/

1. PREP If one thing is underneath another, it is directly under it, and may be covered or hidden by it. 在…下面; 在…底下 

例： The device exploded underneath a van. 那个装置在一辆面包车底下爆炸了。 

例： ...using dogs to locate people trapped underneath collapsed buildings. …利用狗来寻找困在倒塌楼房下面的人。 

2. ADV Underneath is also an adverb. 在下面; 在底下 

例： He has on his jeans and a long-sleeved blue denim shirt with a white T-shirt underneath. 他身穿牛仔裤和一件蓝色长袖粗斜纹棉布衬衫，里面还有件白色T恤衫。 

例： The shooting-range is lit from underneath by rows of ruby-red light fixtures. 射击场被一排排宝石红照明装置从下面照亮。 

3. ADV The part of something which is underneath is the part which normally touches the ground or faces toward the ground. 在下面; 在底部 

例： Check the actual construction of the chair by looking underneath. 看一下椅子的底部来检查它的实际结构。 

例： The sand martin is a brown bird with white underneath. 崖沙燕是一种腹部为白色的褐色的鸟。 

4. N-SING Underneath is also a noun. 下面; 底部 

例： Now I know what the underneath of a car looks like. 现在我知道汽车的底部是什么样子了。 

5. ADV You use underneath when talking about feelings and emotions that people do not show in their behaviour. 在内心 [ADV with cl] 

例： He was as violent as Nick underneath. 他在内心和尼克一样暴烈。 

6. PREP Underneath is also a preposition. 在…内 

例： Underneath his outgoing behaviour Luke was shy. 卢克表面外向、内心羞怯。

</div>

